<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Compliance Attestation — {{ practice_name }}</title>
<style>
@page {
    size: Letter;
    margin: 0.75in;
    @bottom-center {
        content: "Issued by {{ presenter_brand }}.  Verify: {{ verify_phone }} or {{ verify_url_short }}.  Valid until {{ valid_until_human }}.";
        font-family: 'Helvetica', 'Arial', sans-serif;
        font-size: 9pt;
        color: #666;
    }
}
body {
    font-family: 'Helvetica', 'Arial', sans-serif;
    color: #222;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 11pt;
}
.letterhead {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #14A89E;
    padding-bottom: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.letterhead h1 {
    font-size: 26pt;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a365d;
    margin: 0 0 4px 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
}
.letterhead .practice-name {
    font-size: 18pt;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2d3748;
    margin: 0 0 6px 0;
}
.letterhead .period {
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #4a5568;
    margin: 0;
}
.statement {
    margin: 24px 0;
    font-size: 11.5pt;
    line-height: 1.6;
}
.statement p {
    margin: 0 0 14px 0;
}
.signoff {
    margin-top: 36px;
    padding-top: 18px;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
}
.signoff .role-line {
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #2d3748;
    margin: 0 0 6px 0;
}
.signoff .signed-by {
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #2d3748;
    margin: 0;
}
.signoff .signed-meta {
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    color: #718096;
    margin: 4px 0 0 0;
}
.attestation-block {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    background: #f7fafc;
    border-left: 3px solid #14A89E;
    font-size: 10pt;
    color: #4a5568;
}
.attestation-block .label {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2d3748;
}
.attestation-block .hash {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 9pt;
    word-break: break-all;
}
.disclaimer {
    margin-top: 22px;
    font-size: 9pt;
    color: #718096;
    line-height: 1.4;
}
.disclaimer p { margin: 0 0 6px 0; }
.cover-paragraph {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    background: #f0fff4;
    border-left: 3px solid #38a169;
    font-size: 10pt;
    color: #2d3748;
}
.cover-paragraph .label {
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    display: block;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="letterhead">
    <h1>Compliance Attestation</h1>
    <p class="practice-name">{{ practice_name }}</p>
    <p class="period">For the period {{ period_start_human }} through {{ period_end_human }}</p>
</div>

<div class="statement">
    <p>
        This letter documents that <strong>{{ practice_name }}</strong> operates a HIPAA Security Rule technical-safeguard monitoring program reviewed by its designated Privacy Officer, <strong>{{ privacy_officer_name }}</strong>, on a monthly cadence. From {{ period_start_human }} through {{ period_end_human }}, the practice's technical safeguards were monitored on a continuous automated schedule, capturing cryptographically signed evidence aligned to a defined subset of 45 CFR §164.312 technical safeguards and the §164.308(a)(1)(ii)(D) information-system-activity-review control across {{ sites_covered_count }} site{{ 's' if sites_covered_count != 1 else '' }}, {{ appliances_count }} compliance appliance{{ 's' if appliances_count != 1 else '' }}, and {{ workstations_count }} workstation{{ 's' if workstations_count != 1 else '' }}. The full check catalog is available on request.
    </p>
    <p>
        {{ privacy_officer_name }}, as Privacy Officer, reviews the monthly evidence summary. Signed evidence bundles ({{ bundle_count }} for the covered period) and the technical Evidence Kit are available on request to the practice's carrier, legal counsel, or auditor.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="signoff">
    <p class="role-line"><strong>Designated Privacy Officer:</strong> {{ privacy_officer_name }}, {{ privacy_officer_title }}</p>
    <p class="signed-by">Email: {{ privacy_officer_email }}</p>
    <p class="signed-meta">Designation accepted {{ privacy_officer_accepted_human }} (explainer {{ privacy_officer_explainer_version }}).</p>
</div>

<div class="cover-paragraph">
    <span class="label">For the recipient (insurance carrier, board chair, or counsel):</span>
    This letter documents that {{ practice_name }} maintains an active HIPAA Security Rule technical-safeguard monitoring program for the period above. Evidence is preserved in a cryptographically signed chain. To independently verify this letter, call {{ verify_phone }} during business hours or visit {{ verify_url_short }}/{{ attestation_hash[:32] }}. Detailed technical evidence is available on request.
</div>

<div class="attestation-block">
    <p><span class="label">Issued by:</span> {{ presenter_brand }}{{ presenter_contact_line }}</p>
    <p><span class="label">Issued under BAA:</span> dated {{ baa_dated_at_human }} with {{ baa_practice_name }}</p>
    <p><span class="label">Issuance:</span> {{ issued_at_human }} &nbsp;|&nbsp; <span class="label">Valid until:</span> {{ valid_until_human }} (90 days)</p>
    <p><span class="label">Attestation hash:</span> <span class="hash">{{ attestation_hash }}</span></p>
    <p><span class="label">Verify:</span> {{ verify_phone }} or {{ verify_url_short }}/{{ attestation_hash[:32] }}</p>
</div>

<div class="disclaimer">
    <p>This letter is audit-supportive technical evidence. It contains no patient-identifying information and is not part of any designated record set under §164.524. It is not a substitute for the practice's §164.528 disclosure accounting, designated record set, §164.530(d) complaint log, or workforce sanction records. Auditors and carriers may request the Evidence Kit (cryptographically signed bundles + chain + OpenTimestamps anchors) for offline verification. To report a concern, contact compliance@osiriscare.com (best-effort acknowledgment within 7 business days; substantive response within 30 days) or the HHS Office for Civil Rights at hhs.gov/ocr/complaints.</p>
    <p>Evidence bundles are exportable in vendor-neutral format on 30 days' written notice. Attestation-hash verification is supported through the term of the {{ presenter_brand }}–{{ baa_practice_name }} relationship plus a commercially reasonable wind-down period; the practice retains independent copies for §164.530(j) compliance.</p>
</div>

</body>
</html>
